The paper proposes a new class of deep recurrent neural operations for structured objects such as sequences and graphs, and evaluates them on standard applications such as language modeling and molecular graph regression. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-categories of Machine Learning (cs.LG), Computation and Language (cs.CL), Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition (cs.CV), Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI), and Social and Information Networks (cs.SI).
